title: For Sale:  Sig 556R Gen 2 Russian 7.62x39 Piston Operated AK & Troy Rail
postcontent: For sale is a nice Sig 556R Gen 2 7.62x39mm piston operated semi-auto rifle.  It has the TROY quad rail($280 upgrade), Hogue grip($20), comes with 2-30rd.mags and the original polymer stock with rail section and factory top rail in case you remove the Troy rail.  The TROY rail is a must if you plan on doing a lot of shooting as the factory plastic hanguards seem to trap the heat and get hot.  The Gen 2 rifles run like a champ, a couple changes from what I remember researching, they opened up the ejection port more and added the steel magazine catch bar, so you can use polymer or any standard steel AK-47 magazine and not have to worry about it eating away at the aluminum receiver.  You can also run any steel or brass cased ammo through these rifles, hands down the best and most reliable modern AK style platform yet.  Even the new Sig 556xi Russian rifle has had issues from what I've read, "if it ain't broke"...$1,300 in cash or might look at trades.  Only selling
